  <figure class="image-banner">
    <img src="/images/result.jpg" alt="Stump cleanly ground level with the grass after removal" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <figcaption>AQF Level 3 arborists, $20M public liability insured.</figcaption>
  </figure>


  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why a Cardinia arborist (not a bloke with a chainsaw)</span>
      <h2>Three things every Cardinia tree job has to get right.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; max-width: 60rem;">
        <div>
          <h3>The council mapping check.</h3>
          <p>
            Cardinia Shire has a <strong>Significant Tree Register</strong>, plus
            Vegetation Protection Overlays (VPO), Environmental Significance
            Overlays (ESO) and Bushfire Management Overlays scattered across the
            shire. Cut a protected tree without a planning permit and the fines
            start at $9,000 &mdash; sometimes much more if the tree is on the
            register. Most weekend operators don&rsquo;t check. We check the
            council mapping at the quote stage and tell you the moment we see
            anything restrictive. Where a permit is needed we lodge it for you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>The structural assessment, before the climb.</h3>
          <p>
            Before any cuts go in on a mature gum, we walk the tree and look
            for <strong>codominant stems with bark inclusions, included
            branches, fungal brackets, basal cavities, recent cracking, lean
            change since last storm</strong>. Half the trees that fail in
            spring storms had visible defects six months earlier. A 15-minute
            structural assessment up front is the difference between &ldquo;we
            pruned it&rdquo; and &ldquo;we removed it before it removed the
            shed&rdquo;. We tell you what we see honestly &mdash; we don&rsquo;t
            recommend removal when a target-prune will do, and we don&rsquo;t
            prune when the tree is past saving.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>The cut that lets the tree heal &mdash; not rot.</h3>
          <p>
            A correct AS 4373 pruning cut sits just outside the branch collar
            (the slight bulge where the branch meets the trunk). It leaves the
            collar intact so the tree can compartmentalise the wound and seal
            it. A flush cut tears into the trunk and lets decay straight in. A
            stub cut leaves a dead spike that rots back into the trunk over
            5&ndash;10 years. The &ldquo;topping&rdquo; cut &mdash; flat across
            the top of the tree &mdash; is the worst of all: it destroys the
            tree, creates dangerous epicormic regrowth, and is exactly what
            you&rsquo;ll see being called &ldquo;tree pruning&rdquo; on
            Facebook Marketplace. We never top healthy trees.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Service areas</span>
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width: 42rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        Full Cardinia Shire coverage &mdash; Pakenham and the growth corridor in
        the west, Beaconsfield and Officer in the south, Cardinia Lakes and
        Heritage Springs estates, plus the rural east out toward Bunyip State
        Forest and Cardinia Reservoir. Mature gums and storm response are our
        regular weekly work.
      </p>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/pakenham/">Pakenham</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Berwick edge</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Nar Nar Goon</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Tynong</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bunyip</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Garfield</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lakeside</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <figure class="image-banner">
    <img src="/images/detail.jpg" alt="Arborist&#x27;s chainsaw mid-cut close-up" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <figcaption>Council permit handled. Same-day storm response.</figcaption>
  </figure>


  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2>From phone call to clean site &mdash; 5 stages.</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Phone or web</h3><p>Tell us what you&rsquo;re looking at. Storm emergency? We&rsquo;re moving while we&rsquo;re still on the call.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Site visit</h3><p>Free on-site quote within 2&ndash;5 working days (storm response same-day). We walk the tree, check council mapping, give honest options.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Fixed quote + permits</h3><p>Written fixed-price quote. If a planning permit is needed (significant tree, VPO/ESO), we lodge it for you.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>The work</h3><p>JSA &amp; exclusion zone. Climbers up, EWP in if access allows. Chipper, crane or spider-lift as needed. Small jobs same-day, big removals 1&ndash;3 days.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><h3>Clean site</h3><p>Chipped, swept and raked. Mulch removed or left at your option. Stump ground below grade if quoted. Final walk-through.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Need a tree gone? Storm just rolled through?</h2>
        <p>Free fixed-price quote within 2&ndash;5 working days. 24/7 emergency line for storm work.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Articles &amp; guides for Cardinia Shire</h2>
      <p>Practical reading from our jobs in Cardinia Shire &mdash; what we charge, what to watch for, when a callout is worth it.</p>
      <ul class="guides-list">
          <li><a href="/as4970-protection-cardinia/">AS 4970 tree protection on a Cardinia construction site</a></li>
          <li><a href="/council-permit-cardinia/">Council permit for tree removal in Cardinia Shire</a></li>
          <li><a href="/storm-response-cardinia/">Storm tree-down — 24-hour Cardinia response</a></li>
          <li><a href="/stump-grinding-cardinia/">Stump grinding depth for Cardinia builds</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
